
Basic Structure: XXXXX§Option§Arguments
Example: PRINT§Terminal§Please enter nickname:	Prints ‚Please enter nickname:‘ on terminal of client
Example: CHNGE§Nickname§3§Destroyer			Changes nickname of Player with playerId ‚3‘ to ‚Destroyer‘

Section		Command		Option		Arguments				Comments

Terminal	PRINT		Terminal	String message				prints ‚message‘ on the receiver’s terminal



Login		SETTO		Nickname	String nickname				Sets nickname of new player to ‚nickname‘



Lobby 		CHNGE		Nickname	PlayerID player, String nickname, 	changes nickname of ‚player‘ to ‚nickname‘



Chat		CHATM		Global		String message				writes ‚message‘ on the global chat

